<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-701-617  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 701 617.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Dec 10 1990 n620 p91(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ATE world tests job seekers' resolve. (automatic test equipment)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rostky, George.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The job situation in the automatic-test-equipment market is grim.andO;Companies of all sizes are being extremely conservative, hiringonly on an exceptions basis.andP;  LTX Corp has openings for 15engineers at its Westwood, MA, site and seven or eight positionsin San Jose, CA.andP;  The firm is mainly seeking hardware and softwareengineers, but also needs a few manufacturing-test engineers andapplications experts.andP;  ATE Programming Corp in Pompano Beach, FL,expects to do some hiring early in 1991, as does Solid StateMeasurements, located in Pittsburgh.andP;  None of the smallercompanies queried has any plans to hire in the near future.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     EngineeringRecruitmentEmployment OpportunityAutomatic Test Equipment.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>